Wasn't it the Alcatraz loader which drew the screen in blocks rather than line by line? It also allowed for neat touches like a counter or even a scrolling message (Bobby Bearing).  <br /><br />The Players' Pac-Man loader was indeed very clever stuff.<br /><br />Hewson's RanaRama had an interesting loader, too - as the game loaded, the game's backstory and instructions flashed across the screen.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.ysrnry.co.uk/forums/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=76">Cultured_Janner</a> — Sat Sep 03, 2011 1:13 am</p><hr />
