<title type="html"><![CDATA[Sinclair Misc • Re: Loading screen reveals]]></title>

<category term="Sinclair Misc" scheme="http://www.ysrnry.co.uk/forums/viewforum.php?f=6" label="Sinclair Misc"/>
<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.ysrnry.co.uk/forums/viewtopic.php?t=43&amp;p=186#p186"><![CDATA[
Here's a proof of concept - have a set of scripts which runs a hacked version of FUSE loading a TZX in realtime which dumps SCR files for each frame at 25fps for 1.5 mins, then convert the frames to GIF, then analyses the GIFs to figure out when the loading screen reveal is, then puts those GIFs to one side to be turned into an AVI.<br /> <a href="http://www.youtube.com/v/AolA5aFDg8I"></param><param target="_blank"><strong>object</strong></a> <br />Now just need to get it all into one script when can be run in parallel on The Beast so it can deal with lots of TZX files automatically.<br /><br />It's one those those ideas which just won't leave me alone until I act upon it...<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.ysrnry.co.uk/forums/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54">NickH</a> — Sun Jul 31, 2011 12:58 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
