@Warmtoffee;<br />Thanks very much for that.  I have grabbed both listing and .tap file.  It didn't escape my attention that it was you who wrote the program - you clever so and so, you...<br />I shall now settle down for much tinkering and playing with Globe Plotter.<br /><br />As an aside, I know that it is commonplace for us to 'nostalge' over games when discussing the Spectrum, ZX81 or whatever, but for me the overriding fascination is for the listings that were published in the magazines. Everybody could have a go - maybe that's the old Socialist in me rising to the fore - and the results were invariably disappointing (Globe Plotter aside, of course).  I do feel that it is an overlooked (and often maligned) but important aspect of the period. You have made my day with that listing, thanks.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.ysrnry.co.uk/forums/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=77">Meurglys68</a> — Wed Jul 27, 2011 9:16 am</p><hr />
