VU-3d was a terrific program.  I love early 8-bit graphical displays - there is something in their simplicity that I find endearing and aesthetically pleasing.  Maybe its a minimalism that was enforced due to the limitations of the hardware - the stuff we see nowadays is far superior but, I don't know, lacks a wow factor.<br /><br />@Warmtoffee: That Jasper demo of Spectrum Globeplotter was facinating.  I don't suppose you know where I could get hold of the original listing? WoS don't hold Personal Computer World amongst their magazine archives.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.ysrnry.co.uk/forums/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=77">Meurglys68</a> — Tue Jul 26, 2011 7:40 pm</p><hr />
