Emulaters running at 1000% enable me to see what I envisaged back in June 1986 when Spectrum Globeplotter was published in Personal Computer World as a type-in.<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.wearmouth.demon.co.uk/jav/gpdt.htm">http://www.wearmouth.demon.co.uk/jav/gpdt.htm</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Click on the speed bar at the bottom to see the effect. Every pixel is being individually plotted and every pixel on the loading screen is being individually tested too.<br /><br />It transforms any loading screen  though some work better than others  <img src="http://www.ysrnry.co.uk/forums/images/smilies/icon_e_confused.gif" alt=":?" title="Confused" /><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.ysrnry.co.uk/forums/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=69">warmtoffee</a> — Tue Jul 26, 2011 10:21 am</p><hr />
