For me it would have to be &quot;Unclear User&quot;, Crash's near-perfect (but ultimately libellous) spoof of Sinclair User, which resulted in Crash's publisher being sued by the publisher of Sinclair User, (the mighty EMAP, no less).<br /><br /><a href="http://www.crashonline.org.uk/19/unclear.htm" class="postlink">http://www.crashonline.org.uk/19/unclear.htm</a><br /><br />The disputed issue had to be withdrawn to have the offending pages removed (although about 60,000 had already been sold!), and Crash had to publish a grovelling apology. But the row was, ironically, the making of Crash, whose circulation began to rise very rapidly afterwards.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.ysrnry.co.uk/forums/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=76">Cultured_Janner</a> — Sun Jul 10, 2011 9:52 pm</p><hr />
