I do remember the story regarding the colour clash frenzy of <span style="font-weight: bold">House That Jack Built</span>. They put an advert in Crash for it but were furious to find next issue that it was near the back and on the left hand side, always one to avoid. So they phoned up Roger Kean and told him to screw himself because they weren't going to get the money for the advert and since they were going to go bust, Kean would never find them. Hmmm, charming!<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.ysrnry.co.uk/forums/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=70">Spector</a> — Sat Jul 09, 2011 10:30 pm</p><hr />
