With the News Of The World saga exploding in the news this week, I got to thinking about any dirty/dodgy dealings in the Speccy/SAM industry. The worst I could think of was the Imagine collapse (but that was just poor management plus a small bit of manoeuvring ), plagiarism (the Harry Price games) and the odd bit of reviewing preview copies/screenshots. Can anyone come up with any better examples of the worst practices for the Speccy/SAM industry?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.ysrnry.co.uk/forums/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54">NickH</a> — Fri Jul 08, 2011 3:42 pm</p><hr />
