Speedlock, dammit! You know, that pulsing loader that Ocean/US Gold started using in around 1984.  My WHSmith &quot;datacorder&quot; just couldn't cope with the wretched thing.  I had to keep co-opting my ghettoblaster into loading games.  In the end I ditched the old tape player and used the ghettoblaster all the time, as my Speccy loaded absolutely everything that played through it.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.ysrnry.co.uk/forums/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=76">Cultured_Janner</a> — Mon Jul 04, 2011 11:20 am</p><hr />
