For me the one thing that I was glad to see the back of was cassette tape loading. The sense of anticipation waiting 5, 10 or even 15 minutes for a game to load just to watch the machine reset itself was something that sent me into an irate twist. I know things improved with those speed-loader thingies but the advent of the affordable disc-drives could not come fast enough.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.ysrnry.co.uk/forums/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=77">Meurglys68</a> — Sat Jul 02, 2011 6:47 pm</p><hr />
